{"id":69365,"title":"[Urological diseases in a \"general practice\" in the 17th and early 18th centuries].","abstract":"Of national medicohistorical importance was the town physician Johannes Franc (1649-1725). His diary written in Latin gives - among other diseases - an overview of urological diseases affecting citizens in Ulm around 1700. It also allows a look into the \"workshop\" of a scholar who studied contemporary medicine in comprehensive manner. Franc's case reports illustrate a fundamental change in the perception of the patient at the end of the 17th/beginning of the 18th century.","date":"2014-02-18","categories":"Male Urogenital Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24449357","annotations":[{"name":"Medicine","weight":0.673635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medicine"},{"name":"Latin","weight":0.629262,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin"},{"name":"Physician","weight":0.54796,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physician"},{"name":"General officer","weight":0.363374,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_officer"},{"name":"Ulm","weight":0.337999,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ulm"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.333385,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"General practitioner","weight":0.147465,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_practitioner"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.0554043,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Perception","weight":0.0543856,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Perception"},{"name":"Scholar","weight":0.0354412,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Scholar"},{"name":"Century","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Century"},{"name":"Town","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Town"},{"name":"Citizenship","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"htt